race.description: Country Champs Qualifier @ Mtc Feb 28 Mdn Plate
race.comment: MOUNT OGILVIE (5) debuts for the Beasley yard and looked the part in his lead-up trial win, lengthening stylishly through the line. Boudvillain sticks from that hit-out, which is a strong push. Expecting a bright start to his career. WISER (14) has been sound in both runs back without threatening but is nearing peak fitness now. The booking of McDougall is a key lead and he must be taken seriously. DOUBT I'M RICH (2) is a five-year-old son of Rich Enuff on debut for Saab Hasan. Has shown encouraging signs in his lead-up work over the border. Draws well and any market support would be significant. BRICKEE (8) outperformed market expectations last start at Wodonga and has further improvement to come. A minor placing isn't out of the question. SUMMARY (13) is another debutant worth monitoring.
